Clinical officer interns at JM Memorial Hospital, Ol Kalou, have gone on strike. They accuse the administration of mistreating them. They are demanding allowances and off days.The interns say they work seven days a week and say medical superintendent Jackson Macharia ignores them. On Friday, one said, Macharia said he is not concerned about our problems. He said the hospital can run without us. They say they are wrongfully blamed for deaths and corruption. Macharia has also accused the interns of collecting illegal fees from patients. On September 20, Nyandarua Governor Daniel Waithaka told Health executive Peter Mbugua to address cases of patients being referred to private clinics for medical tests.Waithaka said his government has equipped the facilities and no patients should be referred to private hospitals or chemists.